{
  "texts": [
    "The reviewer-centric category detects fake reviews by evaluating the basic behavioral attributes of the publisher rather than the content of the review itself, for example, the social background 16, 17, personal characteristics 18 and behavioral habits 19, 20 of the review publisher.",
    "Recent reviewer-centric research has also focused on detecting reviews written by the same reviewer under different usernames 21.",
    "Metadata can describe relevant information of the data, including time features, ID, length, rating, data, IP address at the time of publication, and date variance of reviews 5.",
    "Metadata can be used to detect unusual reviews.",
    "When a user is identified as an untrusted reviewer, all reviews linked to that user are classified as fake reviews."
  ]
}